{
  "texts": [
    "These types of responses were chosen because they were seen as more digestible for patients with varying levels of health literacy.",
    "For example, one explanation from a dietitian states, \"I like response B better, as it is more clear and relays the information in a more organized way.",
    "It also states \"milk\" instead of \"dairy\", which is more accurate.\"",
    "Equally important was the structure/flow of the responses.",
    "In both domains, responses that were well-organized, such as breaking down advice in a step-by-step manner or logically grouping related information, were considered to be more effective."
  ]
}